    "description": "ðŸš€ **Complete API Collection for Multi-Tenant NestJS Backend**\n\nThis comprehensive collection covers ALL endpoints including the latest features:\n\n## ðŸ†• **Recent Features (NEW)**\n- **Tenant-less User Registration** - Users can register without a tenant\n- **Email OTP Verification** - 6-digit OTP verification system\n- **Tenant Invitation System** - Complete invitation workflow\n- **Tenant Management** - Create and join tenants\n- **Multi-tenant User Support** - Foundation for multiple tenant membership\n\n## ðŸ“‹ **Complete Feature Coverage**\n- **Authentication**: Password, Google OAuth, Account Linking, OTP Verification\n- **Tenant Management**: Registration, Creation, Joining, Google SSO Config\n- **User Management**: CRUD, Role Assignment, Permission Management\n- **Invitation System**: Create, Accept, Bulk Operations, Status Tracking\n- **RBAC System**: Roles, Permissions, Hybrid Permission Model\n- **Notification System**: Multi-channel, Preferences, Real-time, Monitoring\n- **Project Management**: Full CRUD with tenant isolation\n- **System Monitoring**: Health checks, Metrics, Queue monitoring\n\n## ðŸ”§ **Environment Variables**\nAll variables are auto-captured during API interactions:\n- `baseUrl`: API base URL (default: http://localhost:3000/api)\n- `accessToken`: JWT token (auto-captured)\n- `tenantId`: Current tenant ID (auto-captured)\n- `userId`, `roleId`, `permissionId`, `projectId`, `notificationId`: Resource IDs\n- `invitationId`, `invitationToken`: Invitation-related IDs\n\n## ðŸš€ **Quick Start Workflows**\n1. **New User Journey**: Register â†’ Verify Email â†’ Create/Join Tenant\n2. **Existing User**: Login â†’ Access tenant features\n3. **Admin Tasks**: Manage users, roles, permissions, invitations\n4. **Testing**: Use health checks and monitoring endpoints\n\n## ðŸ›¡ï¸ **Security Features**\n- Automatic tenant isolation with x-tenant-id headers\n- JWT token management and validation\n- Permission-based access control\n- Rate limiting compliance\n- Email verification enforcement",
